---
title: Bayou Blackened Chicken Legs with Smoky Red Beans, Buttery Rice & Hot Sauce Crema
description: We could put smoky, peppery, aromatic blackening seasoning on just about anything, but on roasted chicken legs, it’s truly next-level. Why? The spices gain toasty depth in the oven while the meat stays juicy and the skin becomes crispy and crackling. Think it can’t get any better? We added sides of buttery rice and saucy red beans, plus a hot-sauce-spiked crema for drizzling over everything. Time to get a LEG up on dinnertime!
